A TAXI boss belonging to the Midrand Taxi Association was shot dead yesterday. Police Captain Neldah Sekgobela said three people stopped at a tyre repair shop in Tembisa, Ekurhuleni and the occupants of a white Toyota Quantum started shooting at the Ford Figo they were in. Sekgobela said the Figo belonged to the association. According to information the police received, the Quantum was accompanied by a white Corolla. if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");<a href="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" target="_blank"><img src="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" border="0" alt=""></a>“The number plates of the Quantum had been removed. At the moment it is difficult to say whether or not this was a case of taxi violence, as we still do not know who the perpetrators are,” she said. “We are currently still investigating the incident and we hope to make arrests.” A driver in the association was also killed in the shooting, while the third occupant was injured and rushed to hospital. Mphakathi Ndzamba of the association said they were saddened by the murder. “We lost one of our own in a gruesome incident. Things are really bad in the taxi industry at the moment. “We live in fear. We do not know where we can operate safely,” he said. “We do not know the name of the third person, so we cannot say for sure that this was taxi violence.”